23/04/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Court of BiH on Thursday (April 22nd) convicted two Bosnian Serbs of aiding genocide committed in Srebrenica in 1995.
Radomir Vukovic and Zoran Tomic were sentenced to 31 years in prison each in connection with the murder of more than 1,000 people who tried to escape the Muslim enclave.
The two were members of a Bosnian Serb special police unit at the time.
(RTRS, Fena, Dnevni Avaz, BHRT, Reuters - 22/04/10)
